        <h1>Tech Weekly &mdash; June 27, 2026</h1>

        <h2>AI Breakthroughs This Week</h2>
        <p>Researchers at several universities have published findings showing
        that transformer models trained on synthetic data can achieve remarkable
        generalisation across domains. The paper, released on arXiv,
        demonstrates a 40% improvement on standard benchmarks compared to
        previous approaches.</p>

        <p>The key insight from the research is that diversity of synthetic
        training scenarios matters more than sheer volume. Teams that curated
        scenario variety outperformed those that simply generated more data
        of the same kind.</p>

        <h2>Open Source Tooling</h2>
        <p>Open source tooling continues to improve at a rapid pace. The SQLite
        team released version 3.50 with improved full-text search capabilities
        and better WAL mode performance under high concurrency workloads.</p>

        <p>The new FTS5 extensions allow phonetic matching and custom
        tokenizers, making SQLite a more viable option for applications that
        previously required dedicated search infrastructure.</p>
